    "content_hash": "749c26758a7552b2",
    "department": "GTM",
    "description": "Tempo is a layer-1 blockchain purpose-built for stablecoins and real-world payments, born from Stripe’s experience in global payments and Paradigm’s expertise in crypto tech.\n\nTempo’s payment-first design provides a scalable, low-cost predictable backbone that meets the needs of high-volume payment use cases. Our goal is to move money reliably, cheaply, and at scale. Our north star is simplicity for users: fintechs, traditional banks, merchants, platforms, and anyone else looking to move their payments into the 21st century.\n\nWe're building Tempo with design partners who are global leaders in AI, e-commerce, and financial services: Anthropic, Coupang, Deutsche Bank, DoorDash, Mercury, Nubank, OpenAI, Revolut, Shopify, Standard Chartered, Visa, and more.\n\nWe’re a team of crypto-optimists, building the infrastructure needed to bring real, substantial economic flows onchain. Our team primarily works in-person out of our San Francisco and NYC offices. We like to move fast and swing for the fences — join us!\n\nThe Role\n\nTempo is expanding its enterprise footprint across Latin America, and we're looking for a partnerships leader to own that effort. You'll build and scale our regional partner ecosystem; sourcing and closing strategic deals, enabling partners from onboarding through expansion, and serving as the primary commercial and technical bridge between Tempo and the enterprises we work with.\n\nThis is a high-ownership role for someone who thrives in the ambiguity of early-stage market development and knows how to turn relationships into revenue.\n\nResponsibilities\n\n - Own Tempo's enterprise GTM strategy for Latin America, including market prioritization, partner sourcing, and deal execution\n\n - Lead commercial negotiations and structure partnerships that drive mutual growth\n\n - Build deep relationships with technical and executive stakeholders at partner organizations, ensuring smooth onboarding and long-term success\n\n - Collaborate with Product and Engineering to translate partner needs into roadmap priorities\n\n - Design and iterate on scalable enablement programs, documentation, and support playbooks\n\n - Identify integration and co-development opportunities that expand the Tempo ecosystem\n\n - Represent Tempo at regional industry events and within developer and enterprise communities\n\nQualifications\n\n - 7+ years in an enterprise partnerships role including partner sourcing, negotiation, and management with demonstrated ability to lead both technical and commercial initiatives.\n\n - Demonstrated ability to lead both technical and commercial initiatives independently\n\n - Prior experience working with engineering and product teams at blockchain, infrastructure, or fintech startups\n\n - Fluency in Spanish and/or Portuguese; existing relationships in the LatAm market strongly preferred\n\n - Self directed with exceptional relationship building and communication skills. You own your success within both ours and the partners’ organization.\n\n - Experience with B2B or developer-adjacent products (e.g., APIs, dashboards, or partner platforms)\n\nNice to Haves\n\n - Background in payments, stablecoins, or crypto infrastructure\n\n - Familiarity with blockchain concepts such as wallets, data tooling, and settlement rails\n\n - Experience building or scaling a partnerships function from the ground up",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
